            permute(result, i)
            i = 0;
        } else {
            i++;
        }
    }
    
However, I would advise against the one-loop bubble sort, because the algorithm complexity is harder to see (it is still `O(n^2)`, but with only one loop it can give the impression that it is `O(n)`).

